<br>
Evacuate: (Location) spells Port you and your group there quickly. The way Verant has stated, it casts faster than a Portal spell, but there is a slight chance of a group member being left behind. They still maintain this... but in my 60 levels, I've never once left anyone behind on an Evac line spell.<br>
<br>
Portals are just that; group portals to the location stated. Slower casting than Evacs.<br>
<br>
Skyfire and Emerald Jungle are kinda different.. they cast like an Evac &lt;faster than a Portal&gt;, but are just named funky. &lt;Tishan's Relocation is Skyfire, and Markar's Relocation is EJ&gt;<br>
<br>
The spell Lesser Evacuate and later, the level 57 Evacuate are same-zone Evacs.. Look at Graffe for the complete list of where it dumps you. Most often, its used inside dungeons, and it usually dumps you at one of the entrance/exits.. like Sebilis, you land in the entrance.. and Siren's Grotto, Evacuate lands you at the WW/SG zoneline.<br>
Evac and Lesser Evac differ from a regular port in that they take  a slight bit of mana from group members.. Evacuate of course stealing less mana.. but if you're in a situation where you have to Evac, nobody is going to miss that little tick.<br>
<br>
Moon Portals, Gates, and TLs work the same way as any other Port, Gate, or TL... but they have a noticeably longer casting time.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
