<br>
Evacs to specific locations, including Tishan and Markars Relocations (SF and EJ evac spells), can be used from anywhere.  However if you are using Tishan or Markars as a port and you are the only porter around, you might want to port first to a spire, then evac.  This gets you to a safe spire location that you can easily return to if you need to go back for someone.  For example, your group wants to go from, say PoH to EJ--port them to Toxx or Gfay or Nexus with a regular port to be sure everyone is out safely, then proceed with the evac.<br>
<br>
One more thing...at level 39, you may want to give careful thought to whether you really want to go to SF.  The wiz portal there is often crawling with nasties and even at 57, I wouldn't go there without a damage absorb shield--the shield usually allows me enough time to evac or abscond to the zone safe point.  <br>
